<br>
I am looking to get a &quot;open to all&quot; PoA 7th Isle raid setup to get some crowns for us Mages.  Other servers have done these types of raids and from what I have read they all went very well.  I myself am not familiar with leading a PoA raid, Zokof has volunteered to help with this.  Thanks Zokof.<br>
<br>
What to expect:  The spawn time on the island is 24 hours with a typical drop rate of 0-4 crowns per clearing of the isle.  That means we would need to probably spend about 4-5 days there clearing the isle to get a good number of crowns to drop (not counting the time to get to 7th, this is 4-5 days spent ON 7th Isle).  All crowns would be /random 100 for the mages present.  For this to work people who win a crown on the first day on Isle 7 for example would be expected to stay and help the fellow players who helped you get your crown.  It's only fair.  Of course real life takes presidence but you know what I mean.<br>
<br>
What's needed:  I am looking for people to post here with your class, lvl, typical play times, what you have left for epic and any other assistance you can offer be it cash, alts. friends, guild support or whatever.  I will buy the majority of the port stones but you need to provide cash for any keys to be bought and such.  If people have advice on this part please let me know.<br>
<br>
We do need a necro, cleric and monk to attend on this for obvious reasons with hopefully back ups incase one must leave.  A clicky ress cleric would be just ideal as some mobs do death touch.  I am hoping for a guild to take interest and lend a hand who has these classes available.<br>
<br>
There is no set date yet, this is to feel out the interest in such a raid and what I can try to plan for attendance.  Remember this is purely open to anyone to attend but the goal is to hammer to 7th Isle and get crowns.  All loot obtained along the way would be available for random to anyone who helps us Mages get to 7th Isle.<br>
<br>
To clarify this furthur lets say a Spiroc Wingblade drops.  Any non Mage attending the raid may roll on this item.  This is a two fold rule; hopefully this will entice (in this example) some warriors to attend as they may get lucky and win their blade.  Conversely only Mages will be rolling on any crown drops on 7th Island.<br>
